==================================================
CHANGE — Goose baseline for pre-existing schema
Date: 2026-03-30
==================================================

==================================================
GOAL
==================================================

Make service startup migrations work against databases that already contain the
legacy schema but do not yet have goose migration history.

==================================================
WHAT CHANGED
==================================================

Updated:
  internal/infrastructure/postgres/migrate.go

Startup migration flow now:

1. ensures the goose version table exists
2. checks the current DB version
3. if goose reports version 0 but the legacy `users` table already exists,
   inserts baseline version 1 into `goose_db_version`
4. runs normal `goose up`

This treats an existing pre-goose schema as having already applied
`001_init.sql`, while still allowing later migrations such as `002_seed_dev_user.sql`
to run normally.

==================================================
CURRENT STATE
==================================================

- fresh databases still run the full goose migration chain from scratch
- pre-existing databases no longer fail on `relation "users" already exists`
- migration boot is now compatible with the earlier manual-schema / raw-SQL setup

==================================================
VERIFICATION
==================================================

- go build ./...  -> passes
